cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GR (Computer Graphics): The paper deals with processing 3D geometric constraint systems defined on boundary representation (B-rep) models, which is a common topic in computer graphics. 
2. cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper proposes a geometric perturbation method to study free motions of variational B-rep models, which involves computational geometry techniques. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions expressing free motions in terms of composites of several basis motions, which is a common technique in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with 3D models, which is a common topic in multimedia. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper mentions that free motions of a well-constrained model involve more than just rigid-body motions, which is a common topic in robotics.
